\begin_inset Formula 
\[
k_{j}=\overline{q}l_{j}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
where 
\begin_inset Formula $\overline{q}$
\end_inset

 is the average quality level in the economy.
 Borrowing Assumption 1 from AK, only the leader in good 
\begin_inset Formula $j$
\end_inset

 will produce good 
\begin_inset Formula $j$
\end_inset

 at any given time.
\begin_inset Foot
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
This assumption implies that the price will be constant in 
\begin_inset Formula $q$
\end_inset

