\begin_inset Formula $q_{j}$
\end_inset

.
 Alternatively, we could have assumed that 
\begin_inset Formula $k_{j}=q_{j}l_{j}$
\end_inset

.
 Then the CES demand structure would imply that 
\begin_inset Formula $p_{j}=\frac{w}{(1-\beta)q_{j}}$
\end_inset

.
 However, it would not necessarily imply that 
\begin_inset Formula $k_{j}=k$
\end_inset

 as in my 3rd year paper, since we have assumed that 
\begin_inset Formula $q_{j}^{\beta}$
\end_inset

