\begin_inset Formula $q_{j}$
\end_inset

? We can assume they learn how to make machine 
\begin_inset Formula $q_{j}$
\end_inset

 and still preserve this behavior by adding something analogoous to Assumption
 1 here as well.
 If any spin-out has to pay a small cost to play, and we assume that competition
 
\emph on
within 
\emph default
machine line is Bertrand (why? why not?), then no one will spin-out until
 they discover a truly superior quality product.
 
\end_layout

\end_inset

 I conjecture that as soon as an individual acquires this knowledge, they
 will switch their R&D labor supply to a different machine line, since the
 wage will be pushed down by workers willing to work for less in order to
 acquire this knowledge.
 This means that 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\dot{m}_{j}=\nu\hat{l}_{j}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
where 
